headline: How The Narrative Around Quanta Services (PWR) Is Shifting With New Targets And Electric Focus
summary: Quanta Services is back in focus after a refreshed valuation bumped its modeled fair value slightly higher to $479.09 per share, supported by updated views on revenue growth of 12.22% and a modestly higher discount rate of 8.71%. Behind these tweaks, recent Street commentary has leaned more constructive on the company’s long term revenue potential tied to power infrastructure, especially through the Electric division and ongoing acquisition integration.
